@node "Einführung" "Einführung"
   @{u}Introductions@{uu}

   With Etiketti you can make Disk-Labels for for 3 1/2 inch Disks.

   The program reads the Directory of an disk and you can select
   the filenames which will print on the label.

   Etiketti reads Amiga and also PC disks (DD or HD) and prints
   the format on the label.

   Besides you can write a Comment which will print on th label.
@endnode

@node "Systemvoraussetzungen" "Systemvoraussetzungen"
   @{u}Sytemrequirements@{uu}

   Etiketti should run on any Amiga with Kickstart/Workbench 2.04 .
   or higher. To read PC formatted disk and for english localisazion
   you need  Workbench 2.1 or higher. Etiketti is only tested on
   Amigas with Amiga-OS 3.0.

   Etiketti need a NEC oder EPSON compatible printer and should work
   on grafic cards also.
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"
   @{u}Installation@{uu}

   For installing Etiketti copy it in any Drawer you like.

   For installing other Languages except German, you must copy the
   Catalog files to SYS:Locale/Catalogs/<Language>.

   For the Englisch language you must copy Etiketti.catalog from
   Etiketti/Catalogs/English to SYS:Locale/Catalogs/English.
@endnode

@node "Konfiguration" "Konfiguration"
   @{u}Configuration@{uu}

   The configuration of Etiketti is doing about preparing the tooltypes.

   In the current version of Etiketti you only can chose where the programm
   windows will open.

   SCREEN = CustomScreen - Etiketti opens a own screen.
   SCREEN = WbenchScreen - Etiketti opens the programm windows on the
                           Workbench.
@endnode

@node "Bedienung" "Bedienung"
    @{u}Operating Instructions@{uu}

    Gadget:                 Function:

    DF0:                    Read Directory from the disk in DF0.
    PC0:                    Read Directory from the disk in PC0.
    Comment                 Add a Comment.
    Other Disk              Work on another disk..
    Print Label             Print the current label.
    Next Name               Skip the current filename.
    Next Dir                Skip the current directory.
    Accept Name             Accept the current filename for the label.
    Change Name             Change the current filename.
                            The filename is only changed for the label.

    The current filename is showing in the Text-Gadget right from the
    "Accept Name"-Gadget.
@endnode

